    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix segmentation fault when calling nfapi_trace_init() from external modules\n\n### Summary\nWhen attempting to directly call nfapi_trace_init() from external modules, a segmentation fault occurs due to the function being declared as static in debug.c. Additionally, there's a missing string.h include that causes compilation warnings.\n\nThis fix makes nfapi_trace_init() publicly accessible and adds the required header dependencies.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/common/src/debug.c`: Removed static keyword from nfapi_trace_init() and added #include <string.h>\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/common/public_inc/debug.h`: Added declaration for nfapi_trace_init()\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Attempt to call nfapi_trace_init() from any external module that includes debug.h\n2. Observe segmentation fault at runtime due to unresolved symbol\n3. Compilation warnings about implicit declaration of strlen()\n\nThe issue manifests as either compile-time warnings or runtime crashes when external modules attempt to initialize the NFAPI trace system directly.\n"
}